description:
&lt;h1&gt;NHS Supply Chain Officer - London&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At a crucial period of time for UCLH and the NHS, we are looking to recruit experienced Supply Chain Officers to our Bank to work on a dedicated project until March 2021.  This is a “high profile” project to transform store areas across the hospital and improve the service and provision of essential medical equipment to clinical units to support our excellence in patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based at the Main UCLH Tower on the Euston Road, you will work alongside a highly experienced Management Team who will develop your existing Supply Chain skills and provide you with clear instruction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Euston Square and Warren Street Tube Stations face the UCLH Tower and Kings Cross and Euston Mainline Stations are both only a short walk away and the working hours are Monday – Friday 9am – 5pm .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Day-to-day tasks will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data capture of all stock in specific units (detailed stock counting)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relabelling of products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reorganisation of stores&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MS Excel at a basic level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stores/Supply Chain background&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS materials management (desirable)
&lt;p&gt;There are very clear objectives for the project which need to be achieved in a short timescale therefore are looking for candidates that can demonstrate the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A “can do” attitude&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to work well within a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be flexible in their approach to the working day&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Achieving goals and reaching targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you feel you meet the above criteria, please apply on line with your CV and we will be in touch.&lt;/p&gt;
